{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:49:45.388198702Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-be7e91d8","body":"finding_summary: `milestone bead-history` and `milestone tasks` skip the upfront milestone existence check, so a missing milestone is reported as a corrupt record instead of the normal not-found error.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/cli/milestone.rs\nsupporting_references:\n- src/cli/milestone.rs:428-433\n- src/cli/milestone.rs:507-512\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2307-2324\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2374\n- src/adapters/fs.rs:3319-3330\nremediation_hint: Mirror `handle_show()` / `handle_status()` by calling `load_existing_milestone(&FsMilestoneStore, ...)` before invoking `load_bead_execution_history()` or `load_milestone_task_list()`.\nrepro:\n- `cargo run --quiet -- milestone tasks ms-notreal --json` -> `corrupt record in milestones/ms-notreal/milestone.toml: milestone.toml not found`\n- `cargo run --quiet -- milestone bead-history ms-notreal bead-1 --json` -> same corrupt-record error\n- `cargo run --quiet -- milestone show ms-notreal --json` -> `milestone 'ms-notreal' was not found under .ralph-burning/milestones/`","dedup_key":"28e5f6b74006c5fdbc88ed177d9ff390370b82806bc2f0fb34fc5eeda7b90590","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416013140","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:49:45.397440376Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-bb3a8f42","body":"In src/cli/milestone.rs line 995, `run.started_at` uses DateTime<Utc>'s Display trait (formats as \"2026-04-15 15:00:00 UTC\") while `run.finished_at` on the same output line uses `.to_rfc3339()` (formats as \"2026-04-15T15:00:00+00:00\"). This produces two different date formats in the same tab-separated row. The same file's `print_milestone_task_list` correctly uses `.to_rfc3339()` for its date field. Fix: change `run.started_at` to `run.started_at.to_rfc3339()` on line 995.","dedup_key":"30a59b61aa96d74ba00259c1871c16cd0e403bbd57dece13edc42c44e89401f6","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260416013140","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
